data.name: Spicy Vegetable Stir-Fry with Cashew Cream
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant and colorful stir-fry featuring a medley of fresh vegetables and a rich, creamy cashew sauce that adds a delightful twist!
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat sesame oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add minced garlic and grated ginger, saut√© for 1 minute until fragrant.
Add broccoli, bell peppers, carrots, and snap peas. Stir-fry for about 5-7 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
In a blender, combine soaked cashews, lemon juice, soy sauce, and chili flakes. Blend until smooth and creamy, adding water if necessary to thin.
Pour the cashew cream over the stir-fried vegetables. Toss to coat evenly and heat through for another 2-3 minutes.
Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving.
